#### API Summary

#### Client File Retrieval APIs

* [GetGlobalFileList()](#capi-globalfile-getglobalfilelist) - list all global files at the specified `folderPath`
* [GetFileInfo()](#capi-globalfile-getfileinfo) - returns information about the specified file, given a `fileId`.
* [GetFileInfoSimple()](#capi-globalfile-getfileinfosimple) - returns information about the specified file, given a `folderPath` + `filename`.
* [GetGlobalCDNUrl()](#capi-globalfile-getglobalcdnurl) - only required for clients that don't support redirection

#### System File Retrieval APIs

*Accessible via cloud-code and S2S.*

* [SysGetGlobalFileList](#capi-globalfile-sysgetglobalfilelist) - list all global files at the specified `folderPath`
* [SysGetFileInfo()](#capi-globalfile-sysgetfileinfo) - returns information about the specified file, given a `fileId`.
* [SysGetFileInfoSimple()](#capi-globalfile-sysgetfileinfosimple) - returns information about the specified file, given a `folderPath` + `filename`.
* [SysGetGlobalCDNUrl](#capi-globalfile-sysgetglobalcdnurl) - only required for clients that don't support redirection

#### File Management

* [SysMoveToGlobalFile()](#capi-globalfile-sysmovetoglobalfile) - migrate a file from User Files to the Global File system
* [SysCopyGlobalFile()](#capi-globalfile-syscopyglobalfile) - copy a file
* [SysMoveGlobalFile()](#capi-globalfile-sysmoveglobalfile) - move (or rename) a file 
* [SysDeleteGlobalFile()](#capi-globalfile-sysdeleteglobalfile) - delete a file
* [SysDeleteGlobalFiles()](#capi-globalfile-sysdeleteglobalfiles) - delete the contents of a directory

#### Folder Management ####

* [SysLookupFolder](#capi-globalfile-syslookupfolder) - lookup a folder given it's path
* [SysCreateFolder](#capi-globalfile-syscreatefolder) - create a folder
* [SysMoveFolder](#capi-globalfile-sysmovefolder) - move a folder
* [SysRenameFolder](#capi-globalfile-sysrenamefolder) - rename a folder
* [SysDeleteFolder](#capi-globalfile-sysdeletefolder) - delete a folder







